title: Tornodoxa paraleptopalta
text:
Tornodoxa paraleptopalta is a <a href="moth">moth</a> in the family <a href="Gelechiidae">Gelechiidae</a>. It was described by Ueda in 2012. It is found in <a href="Japan">Japan</a> (Honshu, Kyushu).
The forewings are whitish, irregularly tinged with pale brownish grey and scattered with fuscous scales. The dorsal half is tinged with pale brownish grey. The hindwings are light grey.
